Plenty of images of heroic rescues and flooded homes have emerged over the past few days, but nothing shows the scale of the devastation caused by Tropical Storm Harvey than a picture from the air. Photojournalist Marcus Yam of the Los Angeles Times captured images of a flooded downtown Houston and entire neighborhoods submerged in floodwaters. See some of his aerial photos of Houston below. Share this slide: Get top stories and blog posts emailed to me each day. Newsletters may offer personalized content or advertisements.
